content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

To change what supervisors see in Omni Supervisor, use a supervisor configuration to specify which agents, queues, skills, and actions they see. This filters the data used to calculate Wallboard metrics.

You can assign supervisors to a configuration via public groups. Only users with a service presence status assigned to them appear in the Available Users list.

To filter what supervisors see:

* Select visible agents: Add at least one public group to show only those agents.
* Select visible queues: Choose at least one queue to show only those accounts or queues.
* Define visible skills: Select skills to filter the Skills Backlog tab.
* Define actions: Select tabs and move actions to the Selected Actions column (up to 10 per tab).

You can also set up a separate supervisor configuration for each group of supervisors.

To create a new supervisor configuration:

1. From Setup, enter Supervisor Configurations in the Quick Find box.
2. Click New.
3. Enter a name for your configuration.
4. Assign supervisors to the configuration via public groups.
5. Filter agents, queues, skills, and actions as needed.
6. Save.

Note: This configuration doesn't change access to agents, queues, or skills, but filters what they see on Omni Supervisor tabs only.
